{
  "info": {
    "name": "DabApp – Booking Flow (End-to-End)",
    "_postman_id": "dabapp-booking-flow",
    "description": "## Complete booking scenario — client books a trainer session\n\n### Pre-conditions\n- An **approved trainer** exists and has at least one **published course** and one **location**\n- Use the Trainer Module V2 collection to set that up first\n\n### Flow summary\n```\nSTEP 1  Login as user            → {{token}}\nSTEP 2  Browse trainers          → {{trainer_id}}\nSTEP 3  View trainer courses     → {{course_id}}, {{location_id}}\nSTEP 4  Check availability       → pick date + slot\nSTEP 5  Book                     → {{booking_id}}, {{payment_url}}\nSTEP 6  Pay (PayTabs WebView)    → redirect client to {{payment_url}}\nSTEP 7  Check booking status     → payment_status = paid\nSTEP 8  Trainer starts session   → status = in_progress   (login as trainer)\nSTEP 9  Trainer completes        → status = awaiting_confirmation\nSTEP 10 Client confirms          → status = completed, payout triggered\nSTEP 11 Client reviews trainer\n```\n\n### Variables auto-saved by scripts\n`token`, `trainer_token`, `trainer_id`, `course_id`, `location_id`, `booking_id`, `payment_url`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },

  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",      "value": "https://be.dabapp.ma", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token",         "value": "",                      "type": "string",  "description": "Client JWT — saved automatically by Login (User)" },
    { "key": "trainer_token", "value": "",                      "type": "string",  "description": "Trainer JWT — saved automatically by Login (Trainer)" },
    { "key": "trainer_id",    "value": "1",                     "type": "string",  "description": "Saved automatically by GET trainers or GET trainer profile" },
    { "key": "course_id",     "value": "1",                     "type": "string",  "description": "Saved automatically by GET trainer courses" },
    { "key": "location_id",   "value": "1",                     "type": "string",  "description": "Saved automatically by GET trainer profile" },
    { "key": "booking_id",    "value": "",                      "type": "string",  "description": "Saved automatically by POST book" },
    { "key": "payment_url",   "value": "",                      "type": "string",  "description": "Saved automatically by POST book — redirect client here" }
  ],

  "item": [

    {
      "name": "STEP 1 – Auth",
      "description": "Login as client user AND as the trainer. Both tokens are needed for end-to-end testing.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login as client (user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var tok = json.token || (json.data && json.data.token);",
                  "if (tok) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('token', tok);",
                  "  console.log('client token saved');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Login successful', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "  pm.expect(tok).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "login"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"login\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Login as the client who will book the session. Replace credentials with real test account.\n\nSaves `{{token}}` automatically."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login as trainer",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var tok = json.token || (json.data && json.data.token);",
                  "if (tok) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('trainer_token', tok);",
                  "  console.log('trainer token saved');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Trainer login successful', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "login"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"login\": \"trainer@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Login as the trainer who owns the courses.\n\nSaves `{{trainer_token}}` automatically."
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "STEP 2 – Discover Trainer",
      "description": "Client browses the trainer list, views a profile, and picks a location.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET all approved trainers",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var list = (json.data && json.data.data) || json.data || [];",
                  "if (Array.isArray(list) && list.length > 0) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('trainer_id', String(list[0].id));",
                  "  console.log('trainer_id saved:', list[0].id, '-', list[0].name);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('At least one trainer available', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "  pm.expect(list.length).to.be.above(0);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainers",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainers"]
            },
            "description": "Returns all approved trainers. Saves first trainer as `{{trainer_id}}`.\n\nFilter options: `?specialty_id=`, `?level_id=`, `?city_id=`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET trainer profile + locations",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var trainer = json.data || {};",
                  "var locs = trainer.locations || [];",
                  "if (locs.length > 0) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('location_id', String(locs[0].id));",
                  "  console.log('location_id saved:', locs[0].id, '-', locs[0].location_name);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Trainer profile loaded', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "  pm.expect(trainer).to.have.property('id');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainers/{{trainer_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainers", "{{trainer_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Full trainer profile: specialties, level approvals, locations, gallery, reviews.\n\nSaves first `location_id` automatically."
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "STEP 3 – Browse Courses",
      "description": "Client picks which course they want to book. The course_id is used in the booking to auto-fill price and duration.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET trainer published courses",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var courses = (json.data && json.data.data) || json.data || [];",
                  "if (Array.isArray(courses) && courses.length > 0) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('course_id', String(courses[0].id));",
                  "  console.log('course_id saved:', courses[0].id, '-', courses[0].title);",
                  "  console.log('  price:', courses[0].promo_price || courses[0].original_price);",
                  "  console.log('  duration:', courses[0].hours_per_session, 'h');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Courses loaded', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainers/{{trainer_id}}/courses",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainers", "{{trainer_id}}", "courses"]
            },
            "description": "Returns published courses for this trainer. Each course has:\n- `level` (Beginner / Intermediate / Advanced)\n- `hours_per_session` — session duration\n- `original_price`, `promo_price` — use promo if set\n- `total_sessions` — how many sessions in the package\n\nSaves first `course_id` automatically."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET courses by level (Beginner)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainers/{{trainer_id}}/courses?level_id=1",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainers", "{{trainer_id}}", "courses"],
              "query": [{ "key": "level_id", "value": "1", "description": "1=Beginner, 2=Intermediate, 3=Advanced" }]
            },
            "description": "Filter courses by level. Use level IDs from GET /api/trainer-levels."
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "STEP 4 – Check Availability",
      "description": "Client opens the calendar (cal.com-style). The frontend calls this to show which days and time slots are free.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET availability – this week",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var today = new Date();",
                  "var from = today.toISOString().split('T')[0];",
                  "var to = new Date(today.getTime() + 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000).toISOString().split('T')[0];",
                  "pm.variables.set('week_from', from);",
                  "pm.variables.set('week_to', to);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var slots = json.data && json.data.available_slots || [];",
                  "console.log('Available days:', slots.length);",
                  "if (slots.length > 0) {",
                  "  console.log('First available day:', slots[0].date);",
                  "  console.log('Slots:', slots[0].time_slots);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Availability returned', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainers/{{trainer_id}}/availability?from_date={{week_from}}&to_date={{week_to}}&location_id={{location_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainers", "{{trainer_id}}", "availability"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "from_date",   "value": "{{week_from}}" },
                { "key": "to_date",     "value": "{{week_to}}" },
                { "key": "location_id", "value": "{{location_id}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns available time slots for each day in the range.\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"available_slots\": [\n    {\n      \"date\": \"2026-07-05\",\n      \"day_name\": \"Sunday\",\n      \"time_slots\": [\"08:00-10:00\", \"10:00-12:00\", \"15:00-17:00\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"schedule_source\": \"configured\"\n}\n```\n\nThe pre-request script auto-calculates `from_date` (today) and `to_date` (today +7 days).\n\n**Frontend cal.com integration:** Feed `available_slots` into the calendar component. Each `time_slots` entry is one bookable slot."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET availability – specific month",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainers/{{trainer_id}}/availability?from_date=2026-07-01&to_date=2026-07-31&location_id={{location_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainers", "{{trainer_id}}", "availability"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "from_date",   "value": "2026-07-01" },
                { "key": "to_date",     "value": "2026-07-31" },
                { "key": "location_id", "value": "{{location_id}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Full month view — useful for monthly calendar display."
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "STEP 5 – Book",
      "description": "Client selects a date + slot and submits the booking. A payment URL is returned immediately.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST book course session (recommended)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var data = json.data || {};",
                  "if (data.booking_id) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('booking_id', String(data.booking_id));",
                  "  console.log('booking_id saved:', data.booking_id);",
                  "}",
                  "if (data.payment_url) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('payment_url', data.payment_url);",
                  "  console.log('payment_url saved — open in browser to pay');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('Booking created', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "  pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Payment URL returned', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(data.payment_url).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainers/{{trainer_id}}/book",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainers", "{{trainer_id}}", "book"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"course_id\": {{course_id}},\n  \"booking_date\": \"2026-07-05\",\n  \"start_time\": \"09:00\",\n  \"location_id\": {{location_id}},\n  \"notes\": \"First session on a circuit — beginner rider\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Book a specific course. When `course_id` is provided:\n- `duration_hours` → auto-filled from `course.hours_per_session`\n- `price` → auto-calculated from `course.promo_price` (or `original_price`)\n- `level` → auto-filled from the course level\n\n**Response includes:**\n- `booking_id` — saved to `{{booking_id}}`\n- `payment_url` — saved to `{{payment_url}}`, open in WebView for payment\n- `total_price`, `duration_hours`, `start_time`, `end_time`\n\n**Status after this call:** `confirmed` + `payment_status: pending`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST book custom session (no course)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var data = json.data || {};",
                  "if (data.booking_id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('booking_id', String(data.booking_id)); }",
                  "if (data.payment_url) { pm.collectionVariables.set('payment_url', data.payment_url); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainers/{{trainer_id}}/book",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainers", "{{trainer_id}}", "book"]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"booking_date\": \"2026-07-06\",\n  \"start_time\": \"10:00\",\n  \"duration_hours\": 2,\n  \"session_type\": \"beginner\",\n  \"location_id\": {{location_id}},\n  \"notes\": \"Custom hourly session\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Book without a course — manual session. Requires `duration_hours` and `session_type`. Price = `trainer.price_per_hour * duration_hours`."
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "STEP 6 – Payment",
      "description": "After booking, the client pays via the PayTabs URL. In the app this opens a WebView.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET booking status (before payment)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var b = json.data || {};",
                  "console.log('Status:', b.status, '| Payment:', b.payment_status, '| Price:', b.price);",
                  "pm.test('Booking is confirmed', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.status).to.equal('confirmed');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Payment pending', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.payment_status).to.equal('pending');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/bookings/{{booking_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "bookings", "{{booking_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Check booking details before paying. Expected: `status=confirmed`, `payment_status=pending`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST re-initiate payment (if URL expired)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var url = json.data && json.data.payment_url;",
                  "if (url) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('payment_url', url);",
                  "  console.log('New payment URL saved');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/bookings/{{booking_id}}/pay",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "bookings", "{{booking_id}}", "pay"]
            },
            "description": "Generate a new PayTabs payment URL if the original one expired. Returns fresh `payment_url`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET booking status (after payment)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "var b = json.data || {};",
                  "console.log('Status:', b.status, '| Payment:', b.payment_status);",
                  "pm.test('Booking still confirmed', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.status).to.equal('confirmed');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Payment is paid', function() {",
                  "  pm.expect(b.payment_status).to.equal('paid');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/bookings/{{booking_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "bookings", "{{booking_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Call after PayTabs webhook fires. Expected: `payment_status=paid`.\n\n**Note:** PayTabs calls `POST /api/trainer/payments/callback` automatically — you don't need to call it manually in production."
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "STEP 7 – Client Tracking",
      "description": "Client monitors their bookings from the app.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET my bookings (all)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/bookings",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "bookings"]
            },
            "description": "All bookings for the logged-in client, newest first."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET my upcoming bookings",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/bookings?upcoming=true",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "bookings"],
              "query": [{ "key": "upcoming", "value": "true" }]
            },
            "description": "Only bookings from today onward with status pending/accepted/confirmed."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET my confirmed bookings",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/bookings?status=confirmed",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "bookings"],
              "query": [{ "key": "status", "value": "confirmed" }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET my completed bookings",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/bookings?status=completed",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "bookings"],
              "query": [{ "key": "status", "value": "completed" }]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "STEP 8 – Trainer Manages Session",
      "description": "Trainer side — uses {{trainer_token}}.\n\nBooking lifecycle (trainer side):\n`confirmed` → START → `in_progress` → COMPLETE → `awaiting_confirmation`",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET my sessions (trainer)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{trainer_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/sessions",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "sessions"]
            },
            "description": "All sessions for the authenticated trainer. Filter: `?status=confirmed|in_progress|completed`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET single session detail (trainer)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{trainer_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/sessions/{{booking_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "sessions", "{{booking_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Full detail of a session: client info, course, location, payment status."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST start session",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Session started', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{trainer_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/sessions/{{booking_id}}/start",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "sessions", "{{booking_id}}", "start"]
            },
            "description": "Trainer marks the session as started.\n\n`confirmed` → `in_progress`\n\nRequires: booking must be `confirmed` and `payment_status=paid`."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST complete session",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Session completed', function() {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().success).to.be.true;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{trainer_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/trainer/sessions/{{booking_id}}/complete",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "trainer", "sessions", "{{booking_id}}", "complete"]
            },
            "description": "Trainer marks the session as done.\n\n`in_progress` → `awaiting_confirmation`\n\nClient receives a notification to confirm and leave a review."
          }
        }
      ]
